<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-258] docs incorrectly state max client timeout as 60 seconds (it&apos;s based on server ticktime)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-258</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The docs incorrectly state the max client timeout as 60 seconds.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/zookeeper/docs/r3.0.1/zookeeperProgrammers.html#ch_zkSessions&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/zookeeper/docs/r3.0.1/zookeeperProgrammers.html#ch_zkSessions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the current server code has the following logic:&lt;br/&gt;
        if (sessionTimeout &amp;lt; zk.tickTime * 2) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            sessionTimeout = zk.tickTime * 2;
        }
&lt;p&gt;        if (sessionTimeout &amp;gt; zk.tickTime * 20) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            sessionTimeout = zk.tickTime * 20;
        }

&lt;p&gt;So really the docs should say max is 20*tickTime&lt;/p&gt;</description>
